Jeanette Chabalala, News24Train line. (Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Kimberley - Northern Cape police are investigating a case of murder after the body of a 6-year-old boy was found near a railway line in Friedlander Street, De Aar, police said on Friday.The body was found by a passer-by on Thursday morning, said police spokesperson Olebogeng Tawana.Tawana said the boy was last seen on Wednesday, allegedly in the company of his mother's boyfriend.He said the man was still at large."We believe that he could assist the police in this case. Wherever he is he should avail himself or report to the nearest police station or report at De Aar police station," he said.No arrests have yet been made.Anyone with information was asked to contact the investigating officer Captain Matshidiso Mofokeng on 082 455 3873 or 053 632 9545.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.